        "title": "fix(hooks): include media metadata in toPluginMessageReceivedEvent",
        "body": "## Bug\n- Symptom: WhatsApp inbound media is downloaded and included in the canonical inbound hook context, but the `message_received` plugin event drops media fields before invoking plugin hooks. Plugins that listen to `message_received` cannot process images, PDFs, or other attachments.\n\n- Root cause: `toPluginMessageReceivedEvent` omitted `mediaPath`, `mediaType`, `mediaPaths`, and `mediaTypes` from its metadata, while `toPluginInboundClaimEvent` already included them.\n\n## Fix\n- Add the four media fields to `toPluginMessageReceivedEvent` metadata, matching the pattern in `toPluginInboundClaimEvent`.\n\n## Verification\n- New test: media fields present in `toPluginMessageReceivedEvent` ✓\n- Existing tests: 8 passed (9 total) ✓",
